INSTALL

Use docker-compose to run a container.
Optionally, edit the docker-compose.yml and specify any specific addresses/ports(*TODO)

docker-compose up


Manual Install (for pre-alpha):


Server (debian):
apt-get install mongodb ntpdate python-bson 
pip install -r etc/requirements.txt

bin/cmd.sh first_setup
./start

Javascript requirements (distributed with compatible version):

bootstrap
datatables
gridster
lodash
boostrap/modal
d3

Client (debian):
apt-get install wget iw wireless-tools ntpdate
pip install -r client/requirements.txt
cd client
./listen


Now open a web browser to localhost:8080 and enjoy!

-- NOTE - THIS IS SUPER ALPHA SOFTWARE -- RUN IT AT YOUR OWN RISK -- YOU will NOTICE SOMETHING STRANGE ABOUT YOUR CAT AFTER INSTALLING


